results.title: Oil Painting by Roger Edward Kuntz (1926-1975) Famous Listed California Landscape Artist Titled "Pismo Beach" Original Signed by the Artist
results.description:
Oil on board 26" H x 38" W x 1/4" D,  with frame, 32" H x 44" W x 4" D. Marked "Pismo Beach" and "12/71" on the back of the art board and signed "Kuntz" in the lower left corner of the painted side.

My mother purchased the painting in 1972 from the artist at the Claremont Colleges in Claremont, CA.  There was to be an auction of faculty art and my mother saw the painting before the auction and approached Mr Kuntz, struck a deal, directly, left with the painting and proceeded to Clarks Picture Frames and Artist's Materials at 116 Harvard in Claremont and ordered the whitewashed frame and fabric matte shown in the first photo.

From Wikipedia:  "Roger Edward Kuntz (January 4, 1926 – August 22, 1975) was a highly accomplished Southern California landscape painter and a member of the Claremont Group of painters - professors and graduates of Pomona College, Scripps College, and the Claremont Graduate School.[1] A figurative artist with an eye for abstract form, he won critical acclaim for striking compositions that transform an unusual array of subjects, including tennis players, domestic interiors, freeways, road signs, bathtubs and the Goodyear Blimp. A retrospective exhibition of his work, at the Laguna Art Museum in Laguna Beach, CA in 2009, was aptly titled "Roger Kuntz: The Shadow Between Representation and Abstraction". In the exhibition catalogue, curator Susan M. Anderson wrote: "Kuntz's work of the late 1950s and early 1960s quintessentially embodied the experimentation, fragmentation, and paradox in American culture of the time.

Much more here:  http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roger_Edward_Kuntz  or you may Google him yourself.

There will be a substantial difference in crating and shipping costs depending whether or the painting is shipped framed or unframed.  Buyer to pay all costs for crating and shipping.

The shipping costs are merely an estimate.  Actual shipping and crating costs to be paid by buyer.  In the event the actual crating and shipping costs are lower than estimated, the difference will be refunded to the buyer.  Buyer to pay additional costs if higher than the listed quote.

results.title: Lemon Baltic Amber & Rose Quartz Gemstone Knotted Teething Necklace - calming - teething pain relief - self esteem, trauma, crisis help -
results.description:
Genuine Baltic Amber in Lemon and Honey colors with smooth round A Grade Rose Quartz gemstones. This necklace is individually knotted between each bead on 100% silk thread (thread may be white or pink). Necklace fastens with a plastic screw clasp closure which is designed to break if excessive pressure is applied.

*Rose Quartz assists with self-confidence, self-esteem, emotional changes, promoting feelings of self-worth and love; calming, helps in times of trauma or crisis, strengthens the heart and circulatory system and releases impurities from body fluids, plus all Baltic Amber properties!

SHIPS FROM THE USA! (please contact me if you are outside of the USA or Canada for shipping prices)

BALTIC AMBER NECKLACES ARE MADE FOR WEARING, NOT FOR CHEWING!
Please supervise your child while they are wearing the necklace.

Our necklaces are each handcrafted and made of authentic Baltic amber. We will not accept anything less! Please note that these are our stock photos and your specific amber necklace may have some color/shape variations due to the natural elements and hand-made nature of these items.

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

MORE INFORMATION ABOUT BALTIC AMBER TEETHING NECKLACES...
Baltic amber is a natural analgesic (pain reliever) and anti-inflammatory. When it is worn on the skin, the warmth of the skin releases trace amounts of healing oils on the skin. Commonly known as "teething jewelry," Baltic amber has been a natural and traditional European remedy for teething discomfort for hundreds of years. 

Our Baltic amber teething necklaces have been designed to ensure the safety of your child by knotting before & after each bead so in the event that the necklace does break (it is designed to break if excessive force is applied) only one bead will come off and the remaining beads will stay intact. The plastic screw clasp is designed to release if excessive force is applied to the necklace, which ensures the highest safety. Traditional clasps used on children’s necklaces (lobster claw clasp and ring) rely on the ring or necklace breaking to release. The beads on each necklace are small enough that in the event the necklace did break and a bead came loose, it would not present a choking hazard.

Amber teething necklaces can be worn by children aged 3 months to 2 years of age (and up!) - which is typically the time baby teething stops. Getting your baby used to wearing an amber necklace from a young age is a good idea as the earlier the baby starts with the necklace, the easier it becomes a part of them. In fact, most infants and toddlers don't notice they are even wearing one!
Please note that the variations in size are due to the handmade nature of these items. If you are looking for one on the shorter side (or vice versa) please let us know!

PLEASE NOTE: These necklaces contain small parts! The necklaces should be removed from the neck when your child is sleeping. Children should always be supervised when wearing any kind of jewelry.

results.title: Copper and Silver Mokume-Gane Ring with Titanium Sleeve
results.description:
Uber stylish titanium ring features a copper and silver mokume-gane inlay.  Mokume-gane is a mixed-metal laminate with distinctive layered patterns. Translated as "wood-grain metal," the name was borrowed from a pattern created in the forging of Samurai swords and other sharp-edged tools.

The traditional components were relatively soft metallic elements and alloys such as gold, copper, silver, shakudo, shibuichi, and kuromido. After the original metal sheets were stacked and carefully heated, the solid billet of simple stripes could be forged and carved to increase the pattern's complexity. To achieve a successful lamination using the traditional process required a highly skilled metal smith with a great deal of experience.

results.title: Tank a-line colorblock dress with asymmetrical hem- The sunset and the flying birds
results.description:
This summer dress is made of 3 different color fabric- light grey, grey and black. Extra fabric and asymmetrical hem makes a beautiful drape on your thigh!

Story of the drawing:
When the sky over the bay has cleared, my husband can see the beautiful sunset while he drives back from work. At dinner he usually describes how beautiful the color was and how happy he is. He feels the beautiful sunset is a big reward after a hard working day. Looking at his face, I think about an old Chinese poem: “ At the end of the day, the sun go down in the west, the tired birds go back to their nests…”
This design is inspired by this poem. I drew 8 flying birds and one of them is blocking a little bit of the sun. I printed the sun with white ink and the birds in silver ink.

Care: hand wash in cold

Only available in size S, M and L.
